      "message": "It\u0027s not clear why this is necessary. The two possible values of host_if_type are LCP_ITF_HOST_TUN and LCP_ITF_HOST_TAP. Earlier in this function at lines 848-849, it is validated that `hw-\u003ehw_class_index \u003d\u003d ethernet_hw_interface_class.index` when `host_if_type \u003d\u003d LCP_ITF_HOST_TAP`. The `if (host_if_type !\u003d LCP_ITF_HOST_TUN)` here implies that `host_if_type \u003d\u003d LCP_ITF_HOST_TAP`. So `(hw-\u003ehw_class_index \u003d\u003d ethernet_hw_interface_class.index)` should be guaranteed to evaluate true.\n\nAm I misunderstanding something? Can you describe a sequence of configurations that I could use to reproduce a seg fault here?",
